article.headline: UAB 80, Tulane 59
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Tulane coach Shawn Finney saw his team's game Wednesday night with UAB as a culture clash. "We were playing suburban basketball, and they were playing street ball," Finney said. "UAB just out-toughed us. We've got to do a better job against that kind of pressure." Sidney Ball scored 13 points and Carldell Johnson added 12 to lead UAB to a 80-59 victory over Tulane. "I want our guys to be consistent and we were up and down tonight," UAB coach Mike Anderson said. "We had a nice lead but our intensity left us. In the last 6 or 7 minutes, our intensity were there and we were able to pull away." UAB (12-5, 5-1 Conference USA) led 40-33 at halftime and held Tulane without a field goal for the first 5 minutes of the second half. UAB's stingy defense helped give the Blazers a 49-34 lead, but Tulane (7-9,0-5) refused to fold. Two baskets by Marcus Kinzer helped draw Tulane closer, and the Green Wave went on an 11-2 run to cut the margin to 3 points. A follow shot by Vytas Tatarunas made it 60-57 with 17:19 remaining. After a time-out, UAB's Mo Finley hit a 3-pointer that sparked the Blazer's 20-2 run to seal the victory. Kinzer led the Green Wave with 16 points and five assists. Chris Moore hit four 3-pointers and finished with 14 points for Tulane. Demario Eddins and Ronnell Taylor scored 10 points each for UAB. Ball grabbed 11 rebounds and Johnson had 6 assists for the Blazers.
